  "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nI've faced up with following issue: the `eth_getBlockByNumber` request returns empty transactions array for genesis block.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.8.10-stable\r\nGit Commit: eae63c511ceafab14b92e274c1b18bf1700e2d3d\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\r\nGo Version: go1.10.1\r\nOperating System: linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nAPI returns an information about block with its transactions. According to [etherscan.io](https://etherscan.io/block/0) there must be 8893 transactions.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nAPI returns an information about block but the transactions array is empty.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n```sh\r\ncurl http://localhost:8545 -X POST -H \"Content-Type:application/json\" --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_getBlockByNumber\",\"params\":[\"0x0\", false],\"id\":1}'\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Please note**, that this request to the for another blocks (e.g. for 38e9c5) works fine.\r\n\r\nThanks for any help.\r\n\r\n",
